Leaving aside the issue of the efficacy -- or lack thereof -- of spraying
aircraft, am I missing something here re. passengers' RIGHTS? At least to
be informed? Do airlines not have any legal obligation to inform would-be
passengers of their practices, so that those who object can take their
business elsewhere?
--
Fred Ball
<phlab@baynet.net>
